                        <p part="N">卷軸</p>
                        <decoNote>
                                    The handscroll with wide borders (大鑲手卷) features a protective and decorative backing (錦包首) 
                                    crafted from blue silk adorned with brownish-red patterns. The title label (題簽) is composed of 
                                    white Chinese paper. The 'Heaven' section (天) is elegantly fashioned from pale-blue silk, 
                                    displaying signs of damage. Vertical stripes (隔水) are made of white paper. The borders are 
                                    skilfully crafted from pale-blue silk, showing indications of damage. The frontispiece (引首) 
                                    and colophon section (拖尾) are made from traditional Chinese paper, exhibiting delicate signs 
                                    of staining and damage. 
